    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-01-26T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-01-26T10:00:00-05:00" n="79"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d79">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.85/75: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Collier</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-01-26T11:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 26, 1928—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>22. Department’s 8, January 24, 6 p.m. I have finally after repeated
                    representations secured the withdrawal of objectionable provision <pb
                        facs="0234" n="116" xml:id="pg_116"/> from the tariff bill and the bill thus
                    corrected has passed both Houses of Congress.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Collier</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
